=== ROLLBACK: Iteration 2 - Host Network Mode + Remove Avahi ===
Date: 2026-06-29 03:50 UTC (approximately)
Reason: Enable mDNS discovery via host network mode

FILES CHANGED:
1. compose.yaml
   - Removed: ports: section (lines 30-34)
   - Added: network_mode: "host"
   - Purpose: Allow zeroconf broadcasts to reach host network

2. Dockerfile.full
   - Removed: avahi from apk add --no-cache
   - Reason: Unused dependency (Wire-Pod uses zeroconf, not Avahi)
   - Benefit: Reduces image size + CVE surface

3. Dockerfile.slim
   - Removed: avahi-daemon and avahi-utils from apt-get install
   - Reason: Unused dependency (Wire-Pod uses zeroconf, not Avahi)
   - Benefit: Reduces image size + CVE surface

ROLLBACK PROCEDURE (if needed):
1. cd ~/Projects/Docker-Focused-Wire-Pod
2. docker compose down
3. cp ROLLBACK/iteration-2/compose.yaml .
4. cp ROLLBACK/iteration-2/Dockerfile.full .
5. cp ROLLBACK/iteration-2/Dockerfile.slim .
6. ./build.sh --prod
7. docker compose up

EXPECTED OUTCOME AFTER THIS CHANGE:
- escapepod.local resolves without DNS error
- Vector robot can discover the server
- Web UI accessible at escapepod.local:8080
